<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-02-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="502" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Loomis</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-02-13"><hi rend="italic">February 13,
                                    1901</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hill states that the <hi rend="italic">Scorpion’s</hi> visit to the
                            Orinoco to obtain information was in accordance with numerous precedents
                            and without offensive intention.</p>
                        <p>The vessel was ordered to La Guaira, touching at Cumana, Carupano, and
                            Barcelona.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>